Apple overtook Samsung as the world’s top smartphone vendor in the last quarter of 2016. According to data from Strategy Analytics, Apple climbed into first position thanks to its 18% global market share in Q4 2016. Apple shipped 78.3 million smartphones in the quarter, while Samsung sold 77.5 million – 5% lower than the previous year. Samsung maintained first place for annual smartphone sales, although the company’s annual market share is at its lowest since 2011. Huawei earned third place, with a record 10% quarterly market share.